message: Based on reality but a highly sensationalised version. Basically the climbing perch is a pest in Papua New Guinea (to the North of Australia) and has managed to cross two short bits of the Torres Strait (we're talking about 6km/4mi here) to Islands that are Aussie territory. They have a ways to go before getting to the Australian mainland but the ARE a concern.
